    "description": "South Indian Bank South Asia Partners invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Senior Financial Analyst at our Chennai location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout South Indian Bank South Asia Partners:\nSouth Indian Bank South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Prepare MIS reports for senior management review\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Manage accounts payable and accounts receivable functions\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Post Graduate Diploma in relevant field\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Forecasting\n• Proficiency in QuickBooks\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in Income Tax\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n• Proficiency in SQL\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with South Indian Bank South Asia Partners!",
